You need a `Context`. You can get the context from a `Activity`, from a `Fragment` or from a `View`.

Method `onClick(View view)` gives to you a reference of the view which was clicked. So, you can get the context from that view.

For example:

    button.setOnClickListener(new OnClickListener() {
        @Override
        public void onClick(final View viewClicked) {
            Intent intent = new Intent(viewClicked.getContext(), ActivityX.class);
        }
    });

                      
