In WPF, the selection changed event only happens when the value changes.  Dropping down the combo box and clicking on the same entry will not change the selected entry. Therefore no event is fired.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
There are other ways to do what you want but it&#39;s unlikely they are needed.&lt;br/&gt;
One can catch the click event for clicking on an entry in the combobox and process it the same as a selection changed&lt;br/&gt;
